programme.title: Live One-Day International Cricket
programme.sub-title: England v West Indies: Fourth ODI.
programme.desc: England v West Indies. Coverage of the fourth contest in the five-match series, which takes place at The Oval. The home side came out on top the last time these sides met in a 50-over match on this ground. A quickfire 53 from opener Chris Gayle, along with 77 from Dwayne Bravo, helped the Windies set 239 for victory. England eased to that total with eight wickets and five overs to spare, thanks largely to Alastair Cook's 112 from 120 balls

programme.title: Live European Tour Golf
programme.desc: The British Masters. Coverage of the opening day of the event at Close House in Northumberland, where the field battles to succeed last year's champion Alexander Noren. The Swedish player carded a total of 266 - an overall score of 18 under par - last year to finish two strokes ahead of runner-up Bernd Wiesberger. That victory was Noren's seventh on the European Tour, and he would add to his win the following month at the Nedbank Challenge, before winning the BMW PGA Championship in May(n)
